I just voted no. As a legislator for almost 30 years, this may be the worst piece of legislation I have ever voted on. This bill will steal health care from 17 million Americans. This bill will cause hospitals and nursing homes to close and make health care more expensive. This bill will lavish trillions on the wealthy and give painfully little to the middle class in what may be the biggest upward transfer of wealth in U.S. history. This bill will cost $4,000,000,000,000.00. This bill will add trillions of dollars to our national debt. This bill slaps New Jerseyans in the face by refusing to remove the state and local tax deduction cap, a cap which would have expired this year if no action was taken. This bill was produced in the dead of night with virtually no debate, no discussion, no analysis, and no regular order and then rammed through before anyone could actually read it. This is a shameful day for the U.S. Congress.
